---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/seo/Breadcrumbs.astro';

const PRIVACY_VERSION = 'v2.0';
const PRIVACY_LAST_UPDATED = '6 June 2026';
---

<PageLayout
  seo={{
    title: 'Privacy Notice',
    description: 'PoopCheck Privacy Notice. How we collect, use, and protect your data, including your health data.',
  }}
>
  <div class="py-12 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5">
      <div class="mb-8">
        <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Privacy Notice', href: '/privacy/' }]} />
      </div>

      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-2">Privacy Notice</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-10">Version {PRIVACY_VERSION} · Last updated: {PRIVACY_LAST_UPDATED}</p>

      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none
        prose-headings:font-bold prose-headings:text-[var(--color-text)]
        prose-h2:text-xl prose-h2:mt-10 prose-h2:mb-4
        prose-p:text-[var(--color-text-muted)] prose-p:leading-relaxed
        prose-strong:text-[var(--color-text)]
        prose-a:text-[var(--color-accent)]
      ">
        <h2>In short</h2>
        <p>PoopCheck helps you track your gut health. To do that we process your photos, symptoms, and lifestyle answers — some of which is health data. We also use this data to improve our AI, and we may license or sell it to third parties in de-identified form. Accepting these uses is required to use the app; if you do not accept, PoopCheck cannot analyse your scans. You can access, export, correct, or delete your data at any time, and marketing and the sale of raw, identifiable images are always separate and optional.</p>
        <h2>1. What we collect</h2>
        <p>We collect your account details (email, username, sign-in info); your stool images and the symptoms and lifestyle answers you give (health data); the AI analysis we generate from them; basic device and usage data; and your subscription status. We do not collect your precise location, and we do not use cross-app advertising trackers.</p>
        <h2>2. How we use your data (required to use the app)</h2>
        <p>When you use PoopCheck, your data is used to: analyse your scan and give you feedback (using our own AI, and trusted third-party AI to improve accuracy); store your scans so history, charts, and tracking work; train and improve PoopCheck&#x27;s own AI; measure and improve scan accuracy; and produce, license, and sell de-identified insights and datasets to third parties (such as researchers, AI developers, and health and wellness brands). Accepting these uses is required — without your consent the app cannot work.</p>
        <h2>3. Health data and your consent</h2>
        <p>Your scans, symptoms, and lifestyle answers are health data, which the law protects more strictly. We process it on the basis of your explicit consent (GDPR Article 9 and equivalents), which you give before your first scan. Withdrawing this consent stops the processing and, as a result, the app can no longer work for you.</p>
        <h2>4. Optional uses (separate consent)</h2>
        <p>Two things are never required and are always your choice: marketing emails, and the sale of raw, identifiable images to specifically named buyers (for Washington residents, only under a signed, dated authorization). You can refuse or withdraw either at any time without losing access to the app.</p>
        <h2>5. Who we share with</h2>
        <p>We share data with service providers who process it for us under contract (Google/Firebase, Amazon Web Services, RevenueCat, Apple), and with the third parties we license or sell de-identified data to (such as researchers, AI developers, and health and wellness brands). We may also disclose data where the law requires it, or as part of a merger or sale of the business. We do not sell your data for advertising.</p>
        <h2>6. Storage, security, and retention</h2>
        <p>Your data is stored on encrypted servers in the United States, and we strip location metadata from your images. We keep your data while your account is active and delete it within 30 days of account closure, except limited records we are required to keep (such as proof of consent). No system is perfectly secure, but we use industry-standard protections.</p>
        <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
        <p>You can access, export, correct, restrict, and delete your data, and withdraw consent, at any time and free of charge, from Settings or by emailing us. You can also complain to your local data-protection regulator. We do not knowingly collect data from children under 13.</p>
        <h2>8. International transfers, changes, and contact</h2>
        <p>If your data crosses borders (for example, to our US servers), we use appropriate legal safeguards. We may update this notice and will tell you about important changes. Contact us at poopcheck@softallthings.com.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
